I made this recipe tonight and it was Fantastic! I'm vegan so I changed it up a bit..I did add two cloves of garlic, instead of Heavy Cream I added Cashew cream. I also added dried porcini mushrooms, I used the water I reconstituted them with as the vegetable broth. I also did not add the cheese. It was great, not too oily at all. Even my non-vegan family loved it. I would make this again and again.

Rating: 4
My husband, which doesn't like mushrooms, enjoyed this dish very much. So much he he asked me to make it several times since. Instead of red onions I used shallots and used a mixture of shitake and portabello, as I couldn't find cremini.

Rating: 3
Actually 4 forks as I made it: half the olive oil, no added butter at the end and milk instead of heavy cream. To thicken it, I added about a tablespoon of flour at the end of sauteeing the mushrooms and cooked it a bit before adding the broth, etc. Not greasy, still delicious. Oh, and I was out of fresh basil so I added some dried to the cooking mushrooms so the flavor would have time to come out. I was lucky enough to have fresh shitake mushrooms and their flavor really shone in this dish.

