Great basic recipe that's ripe for modification. I used bacon fat with the olive oil and added sliced bacon: delicious. I added 1 diced red pepper too. It gave the red, white and green Italian flag look. I recommend fettuccine versus pappardella.

Rating: 0
This was delicious and very easy. I added two cloves of garlic and instead of using 3/4 cup heavy cream, I used 1/2 cup heavy cream and added 1/4 cup of red wine to cut down on the fat. The red wine added a nice depth to the dish. I thickened up the sauce with cornstarch.

Rating: 4
I made this for a dinner party. It was a hit. I substituted organic regular-sized asparagus and a mixture of portobello and dried porcini mushrooms. I boiled the pasta with some of the water that I used to hydrate the mushrooms. I greatly reduced the amount of cream, butter, and olive oil in response to some of the complaints in other reviews. Delicious!

