Rating: 4
This recipe was fabulous! The only things I changed were - substituted chicken stock for vegetable, added only 1 T of butter and used bow tie whole wheat pasta (half the amount). I also used regular sized asparagus which did not over cook. The pine nuts, basil and parm. cheese really complimented this recipe. I will make this again.

Rating: 4
Sophisticated taste, but easy to make. It's amazing! Make this tonight!!

Rating: 4
I was missing some of the main ingredients, so I changed it up and added my own twist to it. It came out so good I wanted to share it with you. Instead of the onion, mushrooms and pine nuts, I used roasted red bell peppers, garlic and roma tomatoes. Instead of cream, I used goat cheese. First I sauteed the garlic and the peppers, and then added the broth and red pepper flakes. Like the other reviewer, I was concerned about the asparagus getting mushy, so I added them towards the end. Finally, I added the fettucine, goat cheese and tomatoes to the mixture, sauteeing until the goat cheese melted. I topped it all off with grated pecorino. It was delicious. Don't be afraid to experiment with this recipe. It's well worth it.

Rating: 4
Very delicious! I used trenette pasta and added fresh porcini mushrooms to the crimini mushroooms called for in the recipe. I was concerned the asparagus would cook to mush if added when suggested, so I added them in the last two minutes while the sauce was reducing so they were al dente. I doubled the recipe for a group of eight as main course. My guests raved and asked for the recipe.